  "description": {
    "en": {
      "provenance": "imported",
      "value": "To date there has been little research on post trafficking livelihoods or how the issues raised by trafficking intersect with development agendas. IOM in collaboration with Newcastle University, UK and the Non Governmental Organization “Shakti Samuha” is undertaking a research to explore the situation of returnee trafficked women. A key aspect of this research is to gain knowledge that is grounded in the actual experiences of the Nepalese trafficked returnee women themselves and how returnee livelihoods intersect with sexuality and citizenship. Furthermore project facilitates the current debates on the citizenship in the Constitution writing process through ongoing dialogue with relevant subject committees of the Constituent Assembly and Women’s Caucus of the legislative parliament."
    },
    "ne": null
  },
